Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.security.storage.data

Interface ConversionMap<K,​V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Map<K,​V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ColumnMap, XMLMap
    public interface ConversionMap<K,​V>
extends Map<K,​V>
    This is a specific type of map that allows for converting from a data type to a given type. For instance, a ColumnMap contains column names from an SQL table as its keys and the values are the entries, which are strings. A call to getDate(Object) would convert the string to a date object. This encapsulates all the work involved in converting between objects. This is part of the data abstraction layer for all stores.

    Created by Jeff Gaynor
    on 4/16/12 at 12:06 PM
